{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.7",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 7,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 7",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 7 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.7.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:1",
      "text": "Is there not an appointed time to man upon earth? are not his days also like the days of an hireling?",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.7.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:2",
      "text": "As a servant earnestly desireth the shadow, and as an hireling looketh for the reward of his work:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.7.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:3",
      "text": "So am I made to possess months of vanity, and wearisome nights are appointed to me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.7.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:4",
      "text": "When I lie down, I say, When shall I arise, and the night be gone? and I am full of tossings to and fro unto the dawning of the day.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.7.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:5",
      "text": "My flesh is clothed with worms and clods of dust; my skin is broken, and become loathsome.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.7.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:6",
      "text": "My days are swifter than a weaver’s shuttle, and are spent without hope.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.7.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:7",
      "text": "O remember that my life is wind: mine eye shall no more see good.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.7.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:8",
      "text": "The eye of him that hath seen me shall see me no more: thine eyes are upon me, and I am not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.7.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:9",
      "text": "As the cloud is consumed and vanisheth away: so he that goeth down to the grave shall come up no more.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.7.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:10",
      "text": "He shall return no more to his house, neither shall his place know him any more.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.7.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:11",
      "text": "Therefore I will not refrain my mouth; I will speak in the anguish of my spirit; I will complain in the bitterness of my soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.7.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:12",
      "text": "Am I a sea, or a whale, that thou settest a watch over me?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.7.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:13",
      "text": "When I say, My bed shall comfort me, my couch shall ease my complaint;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.7.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:14",
      "text": "Then thou scarest me with dreams, and terrifiest me through visions:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.7.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:15",
      "text": "So that my soul chooseth strangling, and death rather than my life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.7.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:16",
      "text": "I loathe it; I would not live alway: let me alone; for my days are vanity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.7.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:17",
      "text": "What is man, that thou shouldest magnify him? and that thou shouldest set thine heart upon him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.7.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:18",
      "text": "And that thou shouldest visit him every morning, and try him every moment?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.7.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:19",
      "text": "How long wilt thou not depart from me, nor let me alone till I swallow down my spittle?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.7.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:20",
      "text": "I have sinned; what shall I do unto thee, O thou preserver of men? why hast thou set me as a mark against thee, so that I am a burden to myself?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.7.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:21",
      "text": "And why dost thou not pardon my transgression, and take away mine iniquity? for now shall I sleep in the dust; and thou shalt seek me in the morning, but I shall not be.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
